Here is the full **testsmells.org 19-smell catalog** audit of your integration test suite, with integration-test calibration applied.

---

## Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smell Count | Affected Tests |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| High | 2 | 2 |
| Medium | 2 | 2 |
| Low | 0 | 0 |
| **Total** | **4** | **4 (of 8)** |

Framework: **MSTest v4** · Calibration: **Integration** (`[TestCategory("Integration")]`)

---

## Findings by Severity

### 🔴 HIGH — Conditional Test Logic

**Smell #1 (Core Catalog)** · `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` · Line 101

```csharp
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}
```

**Problem:** The `if/else` means only one assertion branch ever executes per run. If `loaded` is never a `PremiumUser`, the discount-rate check is dead code — a hidden testing gap. Integration calibration does **not** downgrade this smell; conditional logic is dangerous at any test scope.

**Fix:** Split into two deterministic tests:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_StandardUser_ReturnsCorrectName()
{
    _repository.Insert(new User("eve@example.com", "Eve"));
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com");

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded.Name);
}

[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_PremiumUser_HasPositiveDiscount()
{
    _repository.Insert(new PremiumUser("eve@example.com", "Eve", discountRate: 0.1m));
    var loaded = (PremiumUser)_repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com")!;

    Assert.IsTrue(loaded.DiscountRate > 0);
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** One branch is likely never tested — false coverage.

---

### 🔴 HIGH — Assertion-Free Test (Unknown Test)

**Smell #4 (Core Catalog)** · `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` · Lines 113–119

```csharp
public void BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }
}
```

**Problem:** Zero assertions. This test passes even if `Insert` silently drops every row. The name suggests a "does-not-throw" intent, but that is not explicitly verified and provides very weak coverage.

**Fix:** Assert on the observable outcome:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void BulkInsert_PersistsAllRecords()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }

    var users = _repository.ListAll();
    Assert.AreEqual(100, users.Count);
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** False confidence — 100 % pass rate with 0 % verification.

---

### 🟡 MEDIUM — Sleepy Test

**Smell #3 (Core Catalog)** · `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` · Line 87
*Downgraded from High → Medium per integration calibration*

```csharp
Thread.Sleep(3000);
```

**Problem:** A hard-coded 3-second sleep makes the suite slower and introduces non-deterministic timing. If the notification takes 3.1 s on CI, the test flakes.

**Fix:** Poll with a timeout instead:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public async Task NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay()
{
    var user = new User("dave@example.com", "Dave");
    _repository.Insert(user);

    using var cts = new CancellationTokenSource(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(10));
    while (!_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id))
    {
        await Task.Delay(100, cts.Token);
    }

    Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id));
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Flaky failures on slower machines and an unconditional 3 s tax per run.

---

### 🟡 MEDIUM — Assertion Roulette

**Smell #11 (Extended Catalog)** · `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` · Lines 35–38

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name);
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email);
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0);
```

**Problem:** Four assertions, none with a message parameter. A CI failure reports only a type like `Assert.AreEqual failed. Expected:<Alice>. Actual:<alice>` — you must open the code to find which property failed and why.

**Fix:** Add descriptive messages:

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded, "User should be retrievable after insert");
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name, "Name should round-trip unchanged");
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email, "Email should round-trip unchanged");
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0, "Database should assign a positive ID");
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Slower triage on CI failures; minor but compounds across a growing suite.

---

## Smells Scanned and Not Found (15 of 19 clean ✅)

| Smell | Status | Note |
|-------|--------|------|
| Mystery Guest | ✅ Clean | In-memory SQLite — no external resource coupling |
| Eager Test | ✅ Clean | No test calls 4+ distinct production methods |
| Magic Number Test | ✅ Clean | `3` and `10` in count assertions are self-documenting (items just inserted) |
| Sensitive Equality | ✅ Clean | No `ToString()` in assertions |
| Exception Handling | ✅ Clean | No `try`/`catch` in test methods |
| General Fixture | ✅ Clean | Both `_connection` and `_repository` are used by all 8 tests |
| Ignored/Disabled Test | ✅ Clean | No skipped tests |
| Duplicate Assert | ✅ Clean | No repeated identical assertions |
| Lazy Test | ✅ Clean | Tests share helper methods (Insert) for setup, but exercise distinct behaviors |
| Constructor Initialization | ✅ Clean | Correctly uses `[TestInitialize]` |
| Default Test | ✅ Clean | Meaningful class name |
| Redundant Print | ✅ Clean | No debug output statements |
| Redundant Assertion | ✅ Clean | No tautological assertions |
| Resource Optimism | ✅ Clean | In-memory DB avoids file-system assumptions |
| Empty Test | ✅ Clean | All tests contain executable code |

---

## Well-Written Tests Worth Highlighting

`DeleteUser_RemovesFromDatabase` and `ListUsers_ReturnsAllInserted` are model integration tests — clear arrange/act/assert, no branching, meaningful assertions, and good names that describe the expected outcome.

---

## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Test | Effort | Action |
|----------|-------|------|--------|--------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` | ~2 min | Add count assertion |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` | ~10 min | Split into two deterministic tests |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` | ~5 min | Replace `Thread.Sleep` with poll loop |
| 4 | Assertion Roulette | `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` | ~2 min | Add message strings to assertions |

Priorities 1–2 fix **false-pass risk** (tests that look green but verify nothing). Priority 3 fixes **flakiness risk**. Priority 4 improves **diagnosability**.
